nodes.title: How to Generate
widgets_values:
0. Write postive/negative prompts and choose CLIP skip
1. Load a checkpoint
2. Choose dimensions for an empty latent image
3. Load any Loras
4. Choose KSampler settings
5. Preview/Save the generation
6. Send the generation to Redraw, Face Swap, or Upscale

nodes.title: How to Condition
widgets_values: The text prompts and CLIP skip apply to both the generate and redraw groups at the same time, or each one alone.

nodes.title: How to use groups
widgets_values:
There are 4 groups: GENERATE > REDRAW > FACE SWAP > UPSCALE in that order.

Each toggle turns a group ON/OFF. When a group is OFF, it is removed from the workflow.

Each group can be used independently from the others.

Ex: enabling Redraw alone lets you upload a local file for img2img.

The result can then move to the next group in the workflow by toggling ON the next group(s).

Any combination of groups can be used!

nodes.title: How to Face Swap
widgets_values:
-1. Don't change settings from previous steps
0. Load and rescale a local image (if using only face swap)
1. Load a face image
2. Preview old image
3. Preview/Save the face swap
4. Send the face swap to upscale

nodes.title: How to Upscale
widgets_values:
-1. Don't change settings from previous steps
0. Load a local image (if using only upscale)
1. Load an upscale model
2. Rescale image to a smaller size
3. Save image to output folder

nodes.title: How to Redraw
widgets_values:
-2. Don't change positive/negative prompts and CLIP skip
-1. Freeze the seed from the previous step (last queued seed)
0. Load a local image (if using only redraw)
1. Load a checkpoint
2. Rescale the latent from previous step to be slightly bigger
3. Load any Loras
4. Choose KSampler settings
5. Preview/Save the redraw
6. Send the redraw to face swap or upscale
